# Single-file non-monotonic DELTA (L2-RDR-018 / L1-EXIT-005 timeline).
#
# Two NORMAL RT15 SA11 Receive records (key 15:11R) whose IRIG timestamps go
# BACKWARD within one file: t0 = 50.500000 then t1 = 50.250000. The per-key
# DELTA tracker must emit DELTA = 0.000000 for the first occurrence and an
# EMPTY DELTA for the second (a negative gap is non-monotonic, not a real
# inter-message delta), plus a one-time "non-monotonic timestamp" WARN.
#
# This is the SINGLE-FILE path (per-reader per-key state); the existing
# merge-non-monotonic-* cases exercise the different merged-timeline path.
# Record bodies are byte-identical to the normal record in
# delta-tracking-irig.hex; only the IRIG timestamp words differ.

# Record 1: normal RT15 SA11 Receive at 192:15:54:50.500000 (first 15:11R).
# TW 0x2402 (type=0x02, Bus A, wc=36) + IRIG (upper 0x180F, middle 0xDB27,
# lower 0xA120).
0224 0F18 27DB 20A1
7E79
0004 0000 0000 2F00 22CA 2F00 22CA
0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000
0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000
0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000
71C7 0078

# Record 2: normal RT15 SA11 Receive at 192:15:54:50.250000 — BACKWARD from
# record 1, so the 15:11R DELTA is non-monotonic and must render empty.
# TW 0x2402 + IRIG (0x180F, 0xDB23, 0xD090).
0224 0F18 23DB 90D0
7E79
0004 0000 0000 2F00 22CA 2F00 22CA
0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000
0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000
0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000
71C7 0078

# end-of-records terminator
0000
